 The population also is significantly older. In 1990, 21.1% was 55 or older, government data said. In 2024, that figure was 30%. Since the 2015 peak, the number of births has fallen annually, and deaths are now outpacing births. There were only 1.22 million live births last year — marginally above the 1999 low. Demographer Alexei Raksha reported the number of babies born in Russia in February 2025 was the lowest monthly figure in over two centuries. 






















